    "example": "Step-by-step instructions to fix the screen not turning on issue on a Dell Inspiron 15 PC:\n\n1. Check the power supply: Ensure that the power cable is securely connected to both the wall outlet and your laptop. Confirm that the charging LED lights up.\n\n2. Perform a hard reset: Disconnect the power cable, remove the battery (if it's removable), and hold down the power button for about 15-20 seconds. Then reinsert the battery (if applicable) and connect the power cable.\n\n3. External display check: Connect your laptop to an external monitor or TV using an HDMI or VGA cable. If the external display works, it indicates a problem with the laptop's LCD screen.\n\n4. Adjust brightness settings: Press the Fn key along with the F key (usually F8 or F9) that controls the display brightness. Try increasing the brightness level to ensure it's not set too low.\n\n5. Update display drivers: Visit the Dell support website, enter your laptop's model, and download the latest display drivers. Install the drivers and restart your laptop.\n\n6. Remove recently installed software or updates: Uninstall any recently installed programs or updates that may be causing conflicts with the display driver. Go to \"Control Panel > Programs > Uninstall a program\" to remove them.\n\n7. Run diagnostics: Dell laptops often have built-in diagnostic tools accessible via a specific key combination during startup. Consult your laptop's manual or Dell's support website for the correct keyboard shortcut and run the diagnostics to identify hardware issues.\n\n8. Contact Dell support: If none of the above steps resolve the problem, it's recommended to reach out to Dell's technical support for further assistance, as it might involve more complex hardware troubleshooting or potential repairs."
