    "example": "Problem: Students struggle with writing essays and research papers.\n\nGPT-powered tool idea: Essay Outline Generator\nDescription: This tool helps students outline their essays and research papers. It prompts the user to provide the main topic and key points, and then generates a well-structured outline based on the input. The outline includes an introduction, body paragraphs, and conclusion, with subheadings and bullet points for each section. This way, students can easily organize their thoughts and ensure a logical flow in their writing.\n\nProblem: Teachers spend a lot of time grading and providing feedback on assignments.\n\nGPT-powered tool idea: Assignment Grader Assistant\nDescription: This tool assists teachers in grading assignments more efficiently by providing automated feedback. Teachers can upload student assignments, and the tool will analyze the text, identify common mistakes, and generate personalized feedback for each student. It can highlight grammar errors, suggest improvements in sentence structure, and even evaluate the clarity of arguments. This way, teachers can save time while still providing valuable feedback to their students.\n\nProblem: Students need help studying and reviewing course materials.\n\nGPT-powered tool idea: Flashcard Generator\nDescription: This tool generates custom flashcards to help students study and review course materials. Users can input a list of terms and definitions, and the tool will create digital flashcards that can be easily accessed on any device. The flashcards can also include images, example sentences, or even audio pronunciations if desired. This way, students can efficiently review and reinforce their knowledge, improving their understanding and retention of the subject matter.\n\nProblem: Language learners struggle with practicing speaking skills.\n\nGPT-powered tool idea: Conversation Partner Simulator\nDescription: This tool provides language learners with a virtual conversation partner to practice their speaking skills. Users can type out their side of the conversation, and the tool will generate responses as if they were interacting with a native speaker. The tool can simulate different scenarios, such as ordering food at a restaurant or discussing a specific topic. This way, language learners can practice their speaking in a low-pressure environment and receive instant feedback on their language usage.\n\nProblem: Students need assistance with generating ideas for creative writing assignments.\n\nGPT-powered tool idea: Story Idea Generator\nDescription: This tool helps students generate creative ideas for their writing assignments. Users can input prompts such as genre, setting, and characters, and the tool will generate unique story ideas based on these inputs. It can provide plot twists, character motivations, and even suggest conflicts or themes to explore. This way, students can overcome writer's block and find inspiration for their creative writing assignments."
